The USB-PD VDM DFU-trigger implementation in
crates/restorekit/src/dfu/vdm.rs is a Rust port of macvdmtool
(https://github.com/AsahiLinux/macvdmtool), Copyright The Asahi Linux
Contributors, which is itself based on ThunderboltPatcher
(https://github.com/osy/ThunderboltPatcher), Copyright 2019 osy86. Both are
licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

This product bundles, as git submodules built from source, the following
libraries, each under its own license (see each project for details, and the
desktop app's About tab for the full license texts):

  libplist, libimobiledevice-glue, libusbmuxd, libirecovery, libtatsu,
  libimobiledevice, idevicerestore .... LGPL-2.1-or-later
  libzip (https://libzip.org) ......... BSD-3-Clause
  usbmuxd (Linux and Windows only) .... GPL-3.0-or-later

Because these libraries are linked statically, the LGPL relink provision is
satisfied by the availability of this project's complete source, which lets
anyone rebuild against a modified library.

Per-platform licensing of distributed binaries
-----------------------------------------------
The restorekit source in this repository is licensed under Apache-2.0. The
license of a compiled binary depends on which components it links:

  macOS binaries (CLI and desktop app) link only the Apache-2.0, LGPL, and
  BSD components above; usbmuxd is not compiled or linked on macOS (the
  system daemon is used).

  Linux and Windows binaries additionally statically link usbmuxd, which is
  GPL-3.0-or-later. A binary that links GPL-3.0 code is, as a combined work,
  conveyed under the GNU General Public License, version 3. GPL-3.0 is
  compatible with Apache-2.0 in this direction, so the restorekit source
  remains Apache-2.0, but the Linux and Windows release binaries as
  distributed are GPL-3.0. Their complete corresponding source is this
  repository.
